Key Match Events: Santi Aldama hit a key 3-pointer with about six minutes left in the fourth quarter to help Memphis reestablish a five-point lead after Utah had rallied out of a 17-point deficit in the second quarter to momentarily go ahead.
Lauri Markkanen netted a game-high 35 points and added nine rebounds, and six other Jazz players scored in double figures.
Morant and Marcus Smart then made key layups in the waning moments to secure the win.
Kessler had a huge game with 16 points, 14 rebounds and five blocked shots.
